remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKPathBuilder` is a mutable accumulator for path operations. Use it to add contours, arcs, curves, and sub-paths before calling <see cref="M:SkiaSharp.SKPathBuilder.Snapshot" /> to create an immutable <see cref="T:SkiaSharp.SKPath" />, or <see cref="M:SkiaSharp.SKPathBuilder.Detach" /> to take ownership of the path and reset the builder.

This type wraps a native Skia resource and implements `IDisposable`. Always dispose when done, either with a `using` statement or by calling `Dispose()` directly.

## Examples

```csharp
using var builder = new SKPathBuilder();
builder.MoveTo(0, 0);
builder.LineTo(100, 0);
builder.LineTo(100, 100);
builder.LineTo(0, 100);
builder.Close();
using var path = builder.Snapshot();
canvas.DrawPath(path, paint);
```
